# Cocktail Timing Benchmark

Below are estimated preparation times for common cocktails from start to finish, including garnishing:

## Quick Cocktails (1-2 minutes)
- Gin & Tonic
- Vodka Soda
- Whiskey Ginger
- Rum & Coke
- Screwdriver
- Cape Cod (Vodka Cranberry)
- Highball variants

## Medium Preparation (2-3 minutes)
- Margarita: 2-3 minutes
  * Mixing time: 1 minute
  * Salt rim preparation: 30 seconds
  * Garnish and serve: 30 seconds
- Daiquiri
- Old Fashioned
- Negroni
- Martini
- Manhattan
- Moscow Mule
- Cosmopolitan
- Whiskey Sour

## More Complex (3-5 minutes)
- Mai Tai
- Pi√±a Colada
- Mojito: 3-4 minutes (due to muddling time)
  * Muddling mint: ~1 minute
  * Mixing ingredients: 1-2 minutes
  * Garnish and serve: 1 minute
- Long Island Iced Tea
- Bloody Mary
- Ramos Gin Fizz
- Mint Julep

## Factors Affecting Preparation Time
- Bartender experience
- Bar setup and tool accessibility
- Pre-prepared ingredients (simple syrup, cut garnishes)
- Complexity of garnishes
- Volume of orders
- Specific preparation methods (shaken, stirred, muddled, blended)

**Synthesis Notes:**
- All META models agreed on the three-tier categorization (quick, medium, complex)
- All models placed the same cocktails in the "quick" category
- There was agreement on placing Mojito in the complex category due to muddling time
- I included detailed preparation breakdowns where multiple models provided similar timing estimates
- I maintained the "Factors Affecting Preparation Time" section which was consistently mentioned
- I omitted specific time estimates where models showed significant disagreement
